<br>
Refl is low endurance, low to hit, medium damage, low bonus to defense<br>
<br>
tendrils is low endurance, medium to hit, medium damage, no defense bonus + new bleed bonus<br>
<br>
Both seem to have similar growth rates... <br>
<br>
So far, nothing has persuaded me to put DTendrils on my quickbar. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=demised>Demised</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Initiate</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#000000>(6/13/03 7:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=258.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.darkhosts.com/demised/trees5.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Reflection vs Tendrils</span><hr size=1> The new bleed damage is substancial... It's almost like a decent weapon buff... <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.darkhosts.com/demised/chainwall.gif"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gaedan>Gaedan</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Initiate</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#000000>(6/13/03 8:22 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=258.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.4th-wall.net/images/pint.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Reflection vs Tendrils</span><hr size=1> I find that Tendrils outweighs Reflection in damage, if only via the bleed.  It is substancial, however, like Demised said, it's just as good as a wiz damage add at times, so why not?<br>
<br>
In duels and PVE, against a slow target, Reflection -&gt; Darkness -&gt; Tendrils/Tendrils/Tendrils is pretty much a guarenteed win for me right now, something around 300-500 points of unanswered damage without damage adds on a yellow/oj.  To be honest, I haven't ever had a chance to test in RvR (I'm in the late 40s exp crunch no rvr for me until 50!), but I imagine that I'll be using DT there and not worry about reflect unless it's a small numbers sort of deal.  With the number of shield tanks I run with, stun isn't really needed.<br>
<br>
Hope that helps.  I'm really enjoying the change, I never used DT before 1.62 since I used to be thrust (weee go 2s stun), but it's my style of choice if I'm tanking.  When I reach 50, things may change with Shadows, but we'll see. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.camelotherald.com/chardisplay.php?s=Palomides&amp;c=265780" target="top"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.4th-wall.net/images/sigs/mertel2.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.4th-wall.net/images/gaedan/">... do i dare disturb the universe ...</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=barlypoptart>Barlypop Tart</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Initiate</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#000000>(6/13/03 8:32 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=258.topic&index=3>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.accucom.net/darien/barly/postal.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Reflection vs Tendrils</span><hr size=1> I use the Reflection &gt; HD combo all the time.. rvr, duels, pve...<br>
I love it, I have high parry to begin with..  38+16 and at one time mastery of parry 2..<br>
<br>
The dmg is nice and the stun helps..  I beat polearms all the time using this (no dirt either)..  no styling till I parry then ref &gt; hd..  run to the side or back and combo thier ass..  Use flurry to finish em off <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Haven't used tendrils much but I love the new bleed on dual shadows.. so in big rvr battles I would use tendrils cause of lagg the 2 combo for a stun be hard to get off. <p><a href="http://www.4th-wall.net" target="_new"><img border=0 src="http://www.4th-wall.net/images/sigs/barlyic.jpg" /></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nirala>Nirala</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>M.C. Hammah</span><br>  Posts: 459<br> <font color=#000000>(6/13/03 9:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=258.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Reflection vs Tendrils</span><hr size=1> I personally never use Tendrils anymore, I use DS for bleed, and since bleeds don't stack there's no advantage to using Tendrils over Ref for me, Ref hits about the same, but uses less endo, think I'm gonna take Tendrils off my qbar. <p>Nirala MistyGloomfortehWIN<br>
