m not really in favor of styles being used to just level up, they should still be useful with a 50 spec.  As it stands now, with 50 spec in DW, Tendrils serves no purpose. <p>Nirala MistyGloomfortehWIN<br>
&lt;The Kindred&gt;<br>
Gawaine<br>
50 Crush Merc<br>
<br>
Kriege<br>
44 Tri-Spec Cleric</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xainder>Xainder</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 69<br> <font color=#000000>(6/13/03 11:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=258.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Reflection vs Tendrils</span><hr size=1> Agreed. The Dual Shadows bleed is amazing how, especially in PvE fighting. When i farm for coin/salavge is like having a Wizards Damage Add on me at all times, since with every swing, it starts the bleed over again at the +25ish damage. And, i swing much faster (even with my Sabre) then the bleed 'ticks', so i can squeeze more damage out of Dual Shadows if i keep hitting with it, instead of letting the 'ticks' count down. And if i have to break out of my Dual Shadows hits to do a Refelction + Hypnotic Darkness chain, then the 'ticks' are still there, chewing away. It really is very nice.<br>
<br>
In RvR, it's not as much of a damage boost, with the super fast fights. But i still like to try and get at least one DS off in a fight if i can manage it. Just tack a Amy. Slash as the back-up style, incase they move or turn, and you're good to go.<br>
<br>
I must say however, Flank <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>NEEDS</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> some form of a to-hit bonus!! I'm really trying to use the side positionals more, but even when i do get into the right spot and let it fly, i'll miss more often then not. If both sides are buffed to the nines, it's that to-hit bonus that makes all the difference to getting the hit, or missing. And this isn't a problem that locking in a Amy. Slash as a back-up will do anything for. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xainder>Xainder</A> at: 6/13/03 11:55 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nirala>Nirala</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>M.C. Hammah</span><br>  Posts: 462<br> <font color=#000000>(6/13/03 9:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=258.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Reflection vs Tendrils</span><hr size=1> Heh, I LOVE DS for farming now, was doin' a quick emerald farm for some stuff for my newly levele'd armsman and I was munchin' through the greens outside of cook room like popcorn.  My bleed almost always starts at 30 and drops 2/tick after, but it was wierd, against one mahr I had my bleed start at 36, never seen it start that high.  I'm kind of curious as to what caused that, I had the sorc in the group hit one with a body based spell to see if it was weak to that damage type, but they're neutral. <p>Nirala MistyGloomfortehWIN<br>
